events.name: Kickoff Event!
events.description:
Hello everyone and welcome to the Google Developers Group at UWM! We are excited to announce our Kickoff Event taking place next week Thursday, May 3 at 6:30pm! We hope to gain some new members and get some ideas from our members about how they would like this group to operate, as well as to discuss potential events for next school year!

This will be our first and only event for this school year, as summer break is approaching soon. We hope that getting a base membership at UWM before the end of the year will help us with gaining some traction quickly so we can get started right away at the beginning of next school year! As a reminder, this group is geared toward UWM students, but anyone is welcome to come!

Note: If you have done development with Google products and would like to speak, host a workshop event, or other ideas next year, we'd love to hear from you at [masked]!

events.name: GDG at UWM's Involvement Fair!
events.description: This event is put on by UWM at the beginning of every year, and we're happy to announce we will be in attendance! This is the perfect time to explore all the student orgs UWM has to offer including GDG@UWM! Come meet us, ask questions about the org, and possibly join us as a member if you're interested!

events.name: Web Dev Basics: HTML and CSS
events.description:
At this workshop, we'll be teaching the basics of web development: HTML and CSS. These technologies are the core parts of every web page but often not a part of CS curriculum. This interactive workshop will give a brief overview of how to create a web page with a full example of recreating the Starbucks website.

This workshop is open to all but geared towards those comfortable with code and no experience in web development. Part 2 in two weeks will cover Javascript, and we'll be using these skills in future workshops such as building a Chrome Extension and learning NodeJS with Firebase.

What to bring:
- A laptop
- Yourself
- A healthy dose of curiosity :)

events.name: Web Dev Basics: JavaScript
events.description:
At this workshop, we'll be teaching the basics of web development: Javascript + JQuery. These technologies along with HTML and CSS are the core parts of every web page but often not a part of CS curriculum. This interactive workshop will give a brief overview of how to create interactive web pages utilizing JavaScript to manipulate HTML and CSS elements on the page and respond to different user actions!

This workshop is open to all but geared towards UWM students who are comfortable with code and have a basic understanding of HTML and CSS (including those who came to Part 1). We'll be using these skills in future workshops such as building a Chrome Extension and learning NodeJS with Firebase.

What to bring:
- A laptop
- Yourself
- A healthy dose of curiosity :)

events.name: Google Careers Talk with Google Engineer Ben Kuehmichel

venue.name: UWM Student Union, Room 191 (2200 E Kenwood Blvd, Milwaukee, WI 53211)
venue.address_1: UWM Student Union, Room 191 at 2200 E Kenwood Blvd

events.description:
Join the Google Developers Group at UWM for a special event featuring Ben Kuehmichel! Ben is a current Senior Software Engineer at Google and UWM alum who has been in the industry for over 10 years and at Google for 7. This talk will be focused on prepping for interviews, working in the tech industry, and Ben's journey from UWM graduate to being a part of one of the tech giants.

There will be time at the end to ask questions, so please feel free to come with some questions you'd like answered!

Note: While Ben initially intended to come to UWM for this talk, he recently had a family emergency and will no longer be able to be here in person. As such, we will be hosting this talk over Google Hangouts in-person.

events.name: GDG Holiday Party! Free bowling, pizza, and raffle!
events.description:
GDG at UWM will be hosting our first GDG Holiday Party this Friday, December 7th! This event is entirely non-technical and will just be a fun time and a way to meet new student members by bowling and eating pizza! We'll also have a raffle where everyone gets 1 entry and each strike you make in your first game gets you another entry. We have 7 Google Home Minis to give away, so be sure to get all those strikes!

The event will take place in the basement of the UWM Student Union at the Union Rec Center. We will have room for 35 attendees and we request that you RSVP if you plan to come. We'll hold your spot for 10 minutes, after which others who come will be able to take your spot. Please only RSVP if you will definitely be there (other than emergencies) as we have a budget to work with and need to get as close to 35 attendees as possible.

All GDG UWM members are welcome to attend this event. Please bring your student ID (or other photo ID if you're not a UWM student) with you as the Union Rec Center will need one in exchange for rental bowling shoes.
events.how_to_find_us: Take the stairs or elevator to the lowest level (I believe called the parking or basement level). Go past the Gasthaus to the end of the hallway and you'll see the Rec Center.

events.name: GDG DevFest Hackathon!
events.description:
Website: https://devfest.uwmgdg.com
Sign Up: https://goo.gl/forms/qgJP1EOQnEMutIKA3

DevFest 2019 is a one-day hackathon where students get together with friends or new people and create something awesome! For our first ever DevFest, we've partnered with Northwestern Mutual to host the hackathon at their Cream City Labs innovation center. The goal will be for teams to build something using a Google service or technology (such as Angular, Firebase, etc.) and within the theme that will be announced at the event (though the themes are only a guideline).

All participants will receive a t-shirt and lunch, in addition to the opportunity to meet Northwestern Mutual recruiters and win up to $500 worth of prizes! All attendees MUST be current students at ANY university/college and over 18 years old.

Agenda

8:30am: Doors open
9:00am: Kickoff announcements
9:15am: Let the hacking begin!
12:30pm: Lunch and NM tour
4:00pm: Presentations begin
4:45pm: Winners announced and closing statements

All attendees MUST bring an ID, and a laptop is highly recommended as this is primarily a programming-focused hackathon (no materials for other projects will be provided, though you may bring your own).
events.how_to_find_us: The entrance is just across from the main tower, just under the skybridge. The gold line runs straight to NM's campus, so we recommend that for most attendees.
